h3. Issue Summary
On the branches page, when trying to create a new branch from a tag, users get the "This link has no power here" error message.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Navigate on Bibucket's UI to a *Repository* > *Branches*;
 # Click *Create branch*;
 # On the *From branch* dropdown, select a tag;
 # Inform the branch's name and click on *Create*.

h3. Expected Results
Customers should get redirected to the recently created branch;

h3. Actual Results
The customer gets a "This link has no power here" error message

h3. Workaround
* This appears to be an issue only with redirecting after the branch creation, so if you go back to the branches visualization and choose to see *All branches*, it will be listed and accessible.

h3. Issue Summary

Currently, if you have the branch permission patterns below, there's no way to delete it on the branch permission BB UI.
 * {{/refs/tags/}}
 * {{/refs/tags/*}}
 * {{/refs/tags/x}}

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create branch permission with the branch name/pattern (either of the following):
 ** {{/refs/tags/}}
 ** {{/refs/tags/*}}
 ** {{/refs/tags/x}}
 # Click *Save*
 # Then it will give an error "An unexpected error occurred"
 # Refresh the page, apparently, it was added
 # Click the (x) button and the item will be gone
 # Refresh the page again, the item is still there

h3. Expected Results

The branch permission item will be deleted
h3. Actual Results

The branch permission item is not being deleted
h3. Workaround

Delete branch permission item using API 2.0.
{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*Step 1: Get branch permission IDs*
 You can use the below CURL command and run it on your end to get your branch permission IDs.
{code:java}
curl -sL -u bb_username:password https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/workspace_id/repo_name/branch-restrictions | jq -c '.values[] | select(.pattern == "/refs/tags/") | .id'
{code}
*Notes:*
 (!) Please do change the {{bb_username:password}} with your real credentials
 (!) Please do change the pattern with the pattern that you want to delete (e.g. */refs/tags/* or */refs/tags/x*)
 (!) Please make sure you have {{*jq*}} installed on your local machine.
 * For Mac: [https://stackoverflow.com/a/49261843]
 * For Windows: [https://stackoverflow.com/a/53967916]{panel}
{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*Step 2: Delete those branch permission IDs*
 You can use the below CURL command to delete those IDs that you'll get.
{code:java}
curl -sL -u bb_username:password -X DELETE https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/workspace_id/repo_name/branch-restrictions/input_id_here
{code}
{panel}
